PHA accumulating microbial community dynamics

Pieter van Veelen

2/24/2022

Description

This is an RMarkdown document containing the analysis of microbial communities comprising PHA accumulating bacteria on wastewater activated sludge. Input data were created by sequencing 16S rRNA gene amplicons using primers 515F and 926R on Illumina Miseq (300 bp PE). Fastq sequence files were analysed using QIIME2 and the feature table, taxonomic assignments, phylogeny and metadata were imported into R. The MiDAS4 was used as reference data for taxonomic assignments. This analysis was published by Estevan Alonso et al. (2022) “url DOI” titled Calcium addition indirectly promotes selective biomass growth and polyhydroxyalkanoate accumulation. This dataset describes the temporal dynamics of PHA-accumulating microbial communities treated with CaOH2 or KOH as feedstock. A different subset of the microbial community is enriched in the first 48 hours in runs with CaOH2 compared with KOH, that caused enhanced PHA accumulation.

The full RMarkdown document is available as RMD file in this repository

Data import

All input data have been created with QIIME2 and are imported in R version 4.0.3. QIIME2 scripts and parameter settings are found in separate bash files that can be found in this Github repository.

Cleaning data set

The following quality control steps are subsequently performed to clean the data: 1) tree resolving using ape package; 2) cleaning up the metadata; 3) replacing taxonomic strings that are empty, NA, metagenome, ambiguous taxa; 4) split blanks from samples;

Rarefaction curves

These curves show how well the sequencing effort captured the diversity in the samples.

# alpha rarefaction curve (https://github.com/MadsAlbertsen/ampvis2/blob/master/R/amp_rarecurve.R)
source("scripts/ampvis2_internals.r")
source("scripts/amp_rarecurve.r")

amp_rarecurve(psdata_AEST, color = "sampleid", legend.position = F, xlim = c(0, 60000))

dev.off()

Fig X. Rarefaction curves. Species denotes number of amplicon sequence variants (ASVs) observed from the unrarefied data. Blank extraction coverage was 44 and the sample with the lowest coverage comprised 26538 reads per sample; a depth at which almost full diversity is captured. Hence, no samples were dropped in later stages.

Fig y Alpha diversity. Estimates are based on rarefied data at 26538 reads per sample, which captured nearly full diversity (see rarefaction plot)

Beta diversity

Abundance-based metrics are ignored due to potential large influence of PCR bias. Principal coordinates analysis (PCoA) of Bray-Curtis dissimilarity and weighted UniFrac

Fig. X. Microbial community composition based on taxon occurrences. Principal coordinates analysis (PCoA) ordination plots of community composition based on A) Jaccard distance and B) unweighted UniFrac distances. Redox conditions applied and initial origin (sample type) both explain variation in microbial community composition. Aerobic conditions, soil-derived and industrial activated sludge-derived microbial commmunities clustered most consitently. PERMANOVA statistics yet to be performed.
